# Normalize line endings to LF for all text files in the repo, regardless of
# the host OS or core.autocrlf setting. Without this, Windows clients with
# core.autocrlf=true write CRLF to disk; tools that enforce LF (Biome's
# formatter, dotnet format) then flag every committed file as misformatted
# and pre-push hooks fail.
#
# `text=auto` lets Git detect text vs binary; `eol=lf` forces LF on the
# working copy for text files. Binary files are unaffected.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit overrides for files that must stay CRLF (Windows-only scripts
# would go here; we don't have any today).

# Common binary types — opt out of any conversion just to be safe.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
